shows.title: NO KINGS
shows.details:
Statehouse Mall Side. They have dehumanized our immigrant neighbors. They have sent masked agents and soldiers to invade our cities, to terrorize, profile, abduct, and disappear hard-working people who have committed no crimes and are performing essential jobs. They have torn apart families. They have trampled the constitution and defied the courts. They have used our tax dollars, enriching their cronies to build concentration camps.

We are rising up in a nationwide, non-violent mass movement. We will not be divided. We will protect our neighbors. We will resist!

Screening and Q&A of Oscar Nominated Short Documentary DEATH BY NUMBERS
shows.details: Join us at the Providence Public Library for a special screening of Oscar nominated documentary short DEATH BY NUMBERS and Q&A with writer and main participant Sam Fuentes. "Death by Numbers" turns an intimate lens on school shooting survivor Sam Fuentes’s journey to reclaim her power, processing trauma through journaling. To prepare for a confrontation with her assailant in his harrowing sentencing trial, she examines complex questions of collective hatred and community justice.

Stone Soup Coffeehouse Presents Catie Curtis
shows.details: Friends took Catie Curtis to concerts at the Stone Soup Coffeehouse while she attended Brown University, introducing her to "under the radar" artists like Cheryl Wheeler and Greg Brown. Curtis gravitated toward the solo acoustic guitar, lyric-driven music, and the sometimes comedic exchange between performer and audience. We promise we’re kept this tradition and it will be a treat to have Catie play The Music Mansion. Tickets are $30 and can be reserved online - check our website.
